  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      An uncontrolled feasibility study on using mouth piece ventilation in palliation of dyspnea&#xD;
      in subjects with incurable advanced disease. Subjects are recruited from a local Hospice and&#xD;
      from oncology ward. The main outcomes are the compliance of the subjects with the treatment&#xD;
      and alleviation of dyspnea during the treatment period.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
